sql:
SELECT AVG(feature_score) AS average_score
FROM city_features
WHERE feature_category = 'Infrastructure';

external_knowledge:
- "Most recent data available" refers to the historical data with the highest year; 
- "Access count" is the total number of times users accessed city data; 
- "Average access duration" is the mean time spent accessing city data; 
- "Download count" and "view count" refer to the number of times city data was downloaded or viewed, respectively; 
- "Average feature score" is a measure of how desirable or attractive a city's features are.

sql:
SELECT feature_name
FROM city_features
WHERE feature_score > 9;
